### The teaching moment for "why replicate?". Run the Categories, SalesOrders,
### SalesOrderLines and SalesProducts replications first (either once up-front
### or via the Federation Monitor tile).
###
### The queries below need `$apply` with `groupby` and `aggregate`. CAP
### rejects these for delegate entities (the remote OData service cannot
### evaluate them). Because `SalesOrderLines` / `SalesOrders` etc. are
### REPLICATED into the local SQLite, the exact same CQL translates to a
### local SQL GROUP BY and works fine.

### Bootstrap — trigger all four replications if you haven't already.
POST http://localhost:4005/pipeline/run
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Categories","mode":"full"}

###
POST http://localhost:4005/pipeline/run
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"SalesOrders","mode":"full"}

###
POST http://localhost:4005/pipeline/run
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"SalesOrderLines","mode":"full"}

###
POST http://localhost:4005/pipeline/run
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"SalesProducts","mode":"full"}

### Revenue per product (local SQL GROUP BY, driven entirely by $apply)
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/SalesOrderLines?$apply=groupby((productId),aggregate(quantity with sum as TotalQty))&$top=10

### Orders per country (a dimension that came straight from Northwind)
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/SalesOrders?$apply=groupby((shipCountry),aggregate($count as OrderCount))&$orderby=OrderCount desc

### Contrast: the same $apply against the DELEGATED `Orders` will fail with
### "Feature not supported" — CAP can't translate groupby to remote OData.
### Uncomment to observe the error.
### GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/Orders?$apply=groupby((shipCountry),aggregate($count as OrderCount))
